    "image_count": 2,
    "description": "\u201cCome and Take It\u201d is a famous slogan from the 1835 Battle of Gonzales, the opening conflict of the Texas Revolution. The phrase originated when Mexican authorities demanded that Texas settlers return a small cannon Mexico had previously loaned them. Instead of complying, the settlers buried the cannon and challenged Mexican troops with a homemade flag showing a star, a cannon, and the words \u201cCome and Take It.\u201d",
    "title": "Tariffs"
  },
